EMERGENT COMPLEXITY :

This project seek studying primal society complexities.

2D world, grid based, each entity is a cell.

entities are configured by these settings :
	energy (at 0 it dies, max 100) (energy controls state also, when low can have more chance going hostile)
	relationship/clan (could be in a group of cells - society) (it also controls state, i would like to see clan wars emerge)
	state (peaceful, vengeance, hostile, scared) (each state changes by luck, this luck augments depending on what happened)
Each entity can move, eat, attack, reproduce.
Entities could die by :
	Energy at 0
	sur-population
	killed by other cell

Energy is gained by eating food.

There are also food as a resource. it augments energy.


I will be using threads as is Thread Pools. It will manage group of cells.

Streams shall be used to calculate metrics. Cell that survived the most, number of deaths, clans created, clans destroyed etc...

Databases are made to store the worlds state, like a save file.

The simulation may be interactive by giving the user a way to build the world. putting food, entities and walls.


Let's get here some group of entities with each a solid task that shape it's actions :

Leader of a clan : other entities follows it (moves beside it)
Reporter : moves high distances, seek food, other clans etc... when it come back near another cell it "share" the information.
warrior : hostile towards other clans
builder : builds farms to produce more food
no-mad : do not have a clan, seek food may be hostile to other entities

================================
STEPS INTO CREATING THE PROGRAM
================================

STEP 1 :
Create the "world" a 2D grid of about 1000 x 1000 pixels. Let's say each pixel can be an entity.
We can zoom in/out

STEP 2 :
Creating one cell
she should be able to move

STEP 3 :
initializing threads to control the world
at this point we should be able to see different cells "moving" on a 2D grid

STEP 4 :
Add in energy food with minor behaviors (searching for food)


